review_blob: Less than $5 a six pack for 16 oz. cans at the local convenience store--how could I go wrong?  Genesee Ice Beer is a corny beer with hints of dead mouse and Elmers glue.  It has an "interesting" oily palate that sticks to the tongue.  This is something to be enjoyed while preparing to commit arson or perhaps acts of public indecency.  If this sounds like you, then drink this beer.  Otherwise, youve been warned.
Mild IPA, not over hopped. Drinkable, sharable, and made for a wide target.
Excellenr raspberry...way better than New Belgiums Frambozen.  Good taste through and through.  If you get a chance, try it!!
Not bad.  Picked this up at the store and enjoyed it thouroughly.  Loved the slight hint of lime.
Smooth, never watered-down taste--but probably should be. Made in the Plank Road Brewery since 1855--and tastes just as old.
I was in the mood for a good dark beer, I got Snow Plow, and I got lucky!  This is a great beer from start to finish.  Not too hoppy, of course, but more than enough malt to make up for it.
Thin flavor, but thats to be expected in a Henrys. Otherwise, pleasant and quite drinkable.

This beer was designed as a microbrew for the macrobrew audience.  With that type of oxymoron as the end goal, it is difficult to know what to expect.  The result, Session is pretty good.  Not as sickly sweet as the average macro, and not as granola as a micro.

This beer is like American Idols final show of the season--it leads you on with a bunch of filler, only to give you what you want at the end.  This beer has a great finish, too bad the start and the middle tastes like your average cheap lager

Got this at the AM.PM.  Only had a couple bucks, so I thought Id give it a try.  At about 3 gulps in, I already feel naseous.  Red Dong is an average, weak-flavored beer that is sappy, yet uncommonly stale.
All the great taste of Pabst Blue Ribbon with non of the unpleasant alcohol effects. I have a 12pack of this in my basement because I know someday someone will consider it a collectors item.
The palate is not complex at all.  Pretty average for a mass-produced Hefe. Good flavor and no off flavors.  Generally unremarkable.

When baby hop plants are planted in the field, they go to sleep each night dreaming of someday being used in a beer like Arrogant Bastard Ale.  Careful when you drink it however, you may go to sleep and wake up with a powerful headache.

Tecate is a Mexican beer.  If your idea of Mexico is Tropical beaches and beautiful Latinas, steer clear of this beer. On the other hand, if your idea of Mexico is abject poverty, donkey meat sold on street corners, and food that will give you the runs for weeks, then this is the Mexican beer for you!!
In terms of all beer, this stuff is next to awful.  But if youve only got a couple of bucks on a hot day and you walk into the 7-11, choose a 24oz of this over a Bud or Coors and you cant go wrong.

Bad flavor, watery metallic taste, sweet aftertaste.  Nothing special, decent color. However,for the pure nostalgia of this beer for me and anyone else who had a point in their life where a good beer was not in the budget and thus opted for the PBR 40 oz., this beer deserves a higher rating.  18 for overall impression.
Not as bad as Haake-Beck, but I cant be 100% certain they didnt just bottle cat urine and call it a near-beer.    If you need an NA, stick to the Amber variety of ODouls or try a Kaliber.

Tastes watered down.  Has off-odors of ermine and weasel.  Thin.  Its a great beer if you want to get drunk all the time but are concerned about your waistline--although if this speaks to you, Id recommend hard liquor.

This beer ours well.  The aroma is of beef jerky.  The flavor and palate leave something to be desired:  I think I can get the same affect by adding a couple drops of Liquid Smoke to a bottle of amber ale.

Smells like a good fruit beer, but the berry taste seems artificial.  It always tempts me if I havent had one in a long time, but tasting it reminds me why I havent had it in a long time.  The appearance is average.
Smelt like a skunk.  Tasted like a skunk.  Maybe the beer was skunked, but nothing will make me touch this again.
Not bad for an NA.  In fact its great for those times when you want a good beer taste and feel but cant drink alcohol.  I like it!

Wonderful apricot flavor.  If you like a fruit beer this one tastes great.  If you dont like fruit beers, dont bother with this as the apricot flavor is front and center.  I like it as a thirst quencher on a hot day.
Cheap!  The local convenience store sells it for $.99/24 oz.  But just the thought of the stuff gives me a headache.  Definitely a chemical smell, like some kind of rug cleaner.
